{
  "text": "the O 3 peak occurs just after June-July when CO peaked at the polluted site Marikana (Fig. A5 ). This observed seasonality in O 3 production signifies the importance of precursor species emissions from open biomass burning during winter and spring in this region, while household combustion for space heating and cooking is also an important source of O 3 precursors, as previously discussed. The strong diurnal CO concentration patterns observed during winter at Marikana (Fig. A5 ) substantiate the influence of household combustion on CO levels, as indicated by [CITATION_1] .",
